de for any amount of time, highest speed wins.\n\n== Using a projector ==\n\nSince the racers are usually facing the crowd, they can\'t see the projected display behind them.  As you might expect, a common racer request is to have monitors in front of them.  With their forehead buried in their stem, LCD screens (heavily covered in a protective Plexiglas box) might work well in between the front and rear rollers.\n\nSending the same image to multiple screens is called \'\'\'mirroring\'\'\'  This can be done with a \'\'\'VGA splitter\'\'\'.  Here are some vendors: [http://www.kvms.com/ KVMs], [http://www.networktechinc.com/ NTI], [http://www.national-tech.com/ National Technology].  Simply do a search for \'vga splitter\' to find more vendors.\n\nTo share the screen with the digital projector in Linux use this command:\n\n > xrandr --auto\n\n== References ==\n\n* [http://www.realtimesoft.com/multimon/faq.asp#Mirroring Multi-Monitor FAQ]','utf-8'),(423,'#REDIRECT [[Fork Stands]]','utf-8'),(424,'== Essentials ==\n\n* Large Venue\n* Two to four Complete Bicycles, minus the front wheel\n* [[Bicycle Rollers]] secured to the ground.  (1 per bike)\n* [[Fork Stands]] secured to the ground.  (1 per bike)\n* [[Roller Sensor Boards]] (1 per bike)\n* Laptop with a \'\'\'two\'\'\' USB ports -- one for Arduino and one for thumb drive setup as described in [[Software Installation]].\n* Colored Ethernet Cables -- goes from [[Roller Sensor Boards]] to Arduino. (1 per bike)\n* Long A/B USB Cable -- goes from Arduino to computer.\n* Digital Projector\n* Projector Screen / Surface\n* Table -- for Laptop\n* Table -- for Projector\n* Chair -- for laptop operator\n\n== Nice to Have ==\n\n* Stage / Platform\n* Gaffers tape -- for preventing tripping on cords.\n* Red and Blue electrical tape -- to mark [[fork stands]].\n* Red and Blue handlebar tape -- to mark the bikes.\n* \'\'\'Long\'\'\' projector cable -- to go from the Laptop to the Projector\n* Spare bike parts & tools:\n** Crankset\n**